Bradford get Wallwork
Wallwork has been unable to get into the West Brom side
Bradford City boss Bryan Robson has finally completed the loan signing of West Brom midfielder Ronnie Wallwork.
Robson has been chasing the former Manchester United man since last week and he will go straight into their squad to play Palace on Saturday.
Wallwork will spend a month on loan at Valley Parade after falling out of favour with Baggies boss Gary Megson at The Hawthorns.
West Brom have already loaned out striker Daniele Dichio to Millwall.
